Here is the website where you can download FFmpeg: https://ffmpeg.org/download.html

Here is the link to installing AFL++ to your machine: https://github.com/AFLplusplus/AFLplusplus

Here is the compilation guide we used to compile FFmpeg on our machines: https://trac.ffmpeg.org/wiki/CompilationGuide

This is the link to the samples that we found to help with our seed corpus: https://samples.ffmpeg.org/

When we had trouble with the error Target Not Instrumented: https://hardik05.wordpress.com/2020/08/22/fuzzing-ffmpeg-with-afl-on-ubuntu/

The author of this blog also has a bunch of youtube videos on Installing and fuzzing with AFL++: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8m6VYjsQUE

This is a link to the OSS-FUZZ project from Google: https://github.com/google/oss-fuzz

